metadata.name: Nativitas
metadata.description: Blood splattered across his feet, ankles, ankles, knees. Blood lazily doused him with vomit and waste, with images long discarded, all worn, tattered, warped, scorched, melted, shattered, eaten up with rust, rotted, soiled, bacterial-eaten and filled with imaginary horror. Now he sat with his face buried in this abomination, and his fear turned into a huge disgusting Something that gutted, gulped him without a trace, and filled again. Filled with something new, something that had been denied up to this point and hidden in the rotting cellars of the soul.
